- AngularJS Supports the Following Two Types Of Storages.

    1.local storage

    2.session storage

local storage.

    As a Developer explicitely we must delete the local Storage.

session storage.

    when ever we close the browser automatically data will be erased from session storage.


- ngstorage is the predefined module used to work the storages.

- ngstorage module have following predefined objects.

    1.$localStorage

    2.$sessionStorage

- $localStorage used to work with the local storage.

- $sessionStorage used to work with the session storage.

- we can store the data in the form of a key & value pairs.


Ex.

$localStorage.mini_project = {"uname":"admin","token":"safhafkjhfkhfk"}; // storing the data in local storage

$scope.var_one = $localStorage.mini_project.uname+"...."+$localStorage.mini_project.token; // Reading the data from the local storage.

delete $localStorage.mini_project;  // deleting the Data from the local storage.



$sessionStorage.mini_project = {"uname":"admin","token":"safhafkjhfkhfk"}; // storing the data in session storage

$scope.var_one = $sessionStorage.mini_project.uname+"...."+$sessionStorage.mini_project.token; // Reading the data from the session storage.

delete $sessionStorage.mini_project;  // deleting the Data from the session storage.

